setBracketMode

public void setBracketMode(int mode)
Specify how '[' and ']' (and '<') are handled. The value - means that '[' and ']' are plain token constituents. The value 0 means that '[' and ']' are equivalent to '(' and ')'. The value 1 means that '[' and ']' are equivalent to '(' and ')', except within a token starting with '<', in which case they are constituents. This is so '[' is non-terminating when reading say ''

setBracketMode

public void setBracketMode()
Specify how '[' and ']' are handled. Overless overridden, uses defaultBracketMode.
